			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Water-based ink</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">水性平版油墨</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Water-based screen printing ink,水性平版油墨</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Materials production</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Organic chemicals</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<sumFormula>Water and pigment</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Water-based ink uses water as a solvent base instead of a plasticizer, as plastisol ink does. It lays down a thin, soft, flexible layer of ink on the garment. These inks are defined as inks that use water as the main solvent for carrying pigment. They are made from water, rather than other components such as plastic or PVC. Water-based inks require a longer drying time during the production process. They can be printed on many mediums and in a variety of different ways.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">水基油墨使用水作为溶剂基，而不像塑溶胶油墨那样使用增塑剂。它能在服装上形成一层薄薄的、柔软的、有弹性的墨层。这类油墨的定义是以水为主要溶剂来承载颜料的油墨。它们由水而不是塑料或聚氯乙烯等其他成分制成。水基油墨在生产过程中需要较长的干燥时间。它们可以在许多介质上以各种不同的方式进行印刷。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
